t\nlikely explanation for our observations. At $z=0.0436$, ASASSN-14ae is the\nlowest-redshift TDE candidate discovered at optical/UV wavelengths to date, and\nwe estimate that ASAS-SN may discover $0.1 - 3$ of these events every year in\nthe future.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 May 2014 20:00:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Sep 2014 17:15:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-11"}
